tag.name: ProgramVersion
tag.description: Version of JPKSPM software that created the file. This tag wasn't written before version 3.1.6

tag.name: FileFormatVersion
tag.description: Version of TIFF-File, version of this table.

tag.name: SavedByProgram
tag.description: The program, that generated this file: 00=other, 01=SPM, 02=IP, 03=SPIP

tag.name: StartDate
tag.description: Start-Date, when Scan was measured or when data were modified or saved. Format: 'yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss zz'

tag.name: Name
tag.description: Name of the sample, a name which indicates the specimen

tag.name: Comment
tag.description: A description of the sample being scanned

tag.name: EndDate
tag.description: End-Date, when Scan was measured or when data were modified or saved. Format: 'yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss zz'

tag.name: Sample
tag.description: Probe info, like a comment

tag.name: UniqueID
tag.description: Identifies every scan in a unique way

tag.name: AccountName
tag.description: Account name of the user who stored the scan

tag.name: Cantilever-Comment
tag.description: Could be used to describe a special coating, etc...

tag.name: Cantilever-SpringConst
tag.description: Spring-constant in [N/m]

tag.name: Cantilever-Calibrated
tag.description: Calibrated is true, if the user has finished a calibration process or decides that the cantilever is calibrated

tag.name: Cantilever-Shape
tag.description: Today two common shapes are available: rectangular and triangular, not used yet!

tag.name: Cantilever-Radius
tag.description: The cantilever tip-radius in [m]

tag.name: ApproachID
tag.description: An identification string that is changed every time the stepper motors are moved

tag.name: FileFormatFeatures
tag.description: Bitmap describing file format features present in this file, as integer converted to a hexadecimal string. See section `Version Numbers`

tag.name: Feedback_Mode
tag.description: Identifies the mode in which the data were collected

tag.name: Feedback_pGain
tag.description: Proportional gain of the feedback-loop

tag.name: Feedback_iGain
tag.description: Integral gain of the feedback-loop in Hz

tag.name: Feedback_Setpoint
tag.description: The setpoint in V

tag.name: Feedback_Approach AdjustBaseline/Feedback_Adjust ReferenceAmplitude
tag.description: Parameters describing the feedback mode contact/intermittent

tag.name: Feedback_Baseline/Feedback ReferenceAmplitute
tag.description: Parameters describing the feedback mode contact/intermittent

tag.name: Feedback_Amplitute
tag.description: Parameters describing the feedback mode intermittent

tag.name: Feedback_Frequency
tag.description: Parameters describing the feedback mode intermittent

tag.name: Feedback_Phaseshift
tag.description: Parameters describing the feedback mode intermittent

tag.name: Tipsaver_Active
tag.description: It is required, if Tipsaver_Setpoint is set.

tag.name: Tipsaver_LowerLimit
tag.description: Not saved yet

tag.name: Feedback_Settings_as_Properties
tag.description: Contains the textual representation of the feedback-settings. Format is as specified in the java.util.Properties object

tag.name: Grid-x0
tag.description: The x coordinates of the (0,0) point of the lattice, in meters measured from the center of the area accessable by the instrument

tag.name: Grid-y0
tag.description: The y coordinates of the (0,0) point of the lattice, in meters measured from the center of the area accessable by the instrument

tag.name: Grid-uLength
tag.description: Length of the grid in the fast-direction, [m]

tag.name: Grid-vLength
tag.description: Length of the grid in the slow-direction, [m]

tag.name: Grid-Theta
tag.description: Angle of the fast axis measured relative to the x axis, in radians

tag.name: Grid-Reflect
tag.description: Is the grid mirror reflected, making (u,v) a left-handed coordinate system? (If so, the v axis points in direction opposite to normal)

tag.name: Grid-iLength
tag.description: The number of pixels in the fast direction

tag.name: Grid-jLength
tag.description: The number of pixels in the slow direction

tag.name: Lineend
tag.description: Type of TimingSettings

tag.name: Scanrate-Frequency
tag.description: Scanrate of a whole trace and retrace including the overscan defined by dutyCycle

tag.name: Motion
tag.description: 'topDown' means that the scan was taken in the direction of increasing jIndex; 'bottomUp' means jIndex was decreasing. Please note that the names do not agree with the way that images are drawn in the GUI!

tag.name: Scanline-Start
tag.description: Reserved

tag.name: Scanline-Size
tag.description: Reserved

tag.name: Delay
tag.description: Delay of TimingSettings [in seconds]

tag.name: PauseAtEnd
tag.description: Describes ForceTimingSettings

tag.name: PauseAtStart
tag.description: Describes ForceTimingSettings

tag.name: PauseOnTipsaver
tag.description: Describes ForceTimingSettings

tag.name: TraceScantime
tag.description: Describes ForceTimingSettings

tag.name: RetraceScantime
tag.description: Describes ForceTimingSettings

tag.name: Z-Start-Pause-Option
tag.description: Describes ForceScanningPaseOption

tag.name: Z-End-Pause-Option
tag.description: Describes ForceScanningPaseOption

tag.name: Tipsaver-Pause-Option
tag.description: Describes the ForceScanningPauseOption

tag.name: PauseBeforeFirst
tag.description: Describes ForceTimingSettings

tag.name: Scanner
tag.description: Stage used for x/y scanning. 0 designates the tip scanner. Deprecated starting in version 0.9, replaced by ScannerPositions.

tag.name: FitAlgorithmName
tag.description: Describes the ForceScanFitAlgorithm used to fit this data (this option is only used in force map images)

tag.name: LastIndex
tag.description: [Obsolete] The last index (Nx × Ny - 1) of the grid.

tag.name: BackAndForth
tag.description: The direction the grid is organized.

tag.name: ForceSettings as Properties
tag.description: Contains the textual representation of the force-distance -settings. Format is as specified in the java.util.Properties object.

tag.name: NrOfSlots
tag.description: FeedbackModeInfo: Number of CalibrationSlots that are stored in the CalibrationSet.

tag.name: DefaultSlot
tag.description: FeedbackModeInfo: The name of the calibration slot that was selected.

tag.name: Slot-Name
tag.description: FeedbackModeInfo: Name of this CalibrationSlot.

tag.name: Slot-Type
tag.description: FeedbackModeInfo: Type of the current CalibrationSlot. If the type is relative, Slot-Parent must be defined.

tag.name: Slot-Parent
tag.description: FeedbackModeInfo: Defines the CalibrationSlot that is the base or current CalibrationSlot.

tag.name: Calibration-Name
tag.description: FeedbackModeInfo: Name of the calibration that contains the used encoder, i.e. 'unknown - Calibration'

tag.name: Encoder-Name
tag.description: FeedbackModeInfo: Name of the encoder that defines the scaling for imagedata, e.g. 'SignedShort','UnsignedShort'

tag.name: Encoder-Unit
tag.description: FeedbackModeInfo: Physical unit of the scan data: 'V/m' 'N' etc.

tag.name: Scaling-Type
tag.description: FeedbackModeInfo: Type of the scaling: This defines how the imagedata have to be interpreted. Example: 'LinearScaling'.

tag.name: Scaling-Multiply
tag.description: Only for LinearScaling: The data in this slot are given by a inear scaling from the raw data using ''value = Scaling-Offset + Scaling-Multiply * raw''

tag.name: Scaling-Offset
tag.description: Only for LinearScaling: The data in this slot are given by a inear scaling from the raw data using ''value = Scaling-Offset + Scaling-Multiply * raw''

tag.name: Channel
tag.description: Name of the channel, e.g. height

tag.name: Channel-retrace
tag.description: Direction of measurement; 0 for trace, 1 for retrace

tag.name: ChannelFancyName
tag.description: Easy-to-read name for this channel.

tag.name: ChannelStyle
tag.description: The ChannelStyle object as properties.

tag.name: Calibration_age
tag.description: Is given in days since the selected calibration.

tag.name: Calibration_operator
tag.description: It is an element for later extensions (e.g. comments to own calibration standards).

tag.name: NrOfSlots
tag.description: Number of CalibrationSlots stored in the CalibrationSet.

tag.name: DefaultSlots
tag.description: Indicates the Slot(name), which is selected.

tag.name: Slot-Name
tag.description: Name of the current CalibrationSlot.

tag.name: Slot-Type
tag.description: Type of the current CalibrationSlot; it may be absolute or relative. If the type is relative, then Slot-Parent must be defined.

tag.name: Slot-Parent
tag.description: Defines the CalibrationSlot relative to which this slot was defined.

tag.name: Calibration-Name
tag.description: Name of the calibration that contains the used encoder. Default: 'unknown - Calibration'.

tag.name: Encoder-Name
tag.description: The type of data stored in the image. Currently this is one of 'UnsignedShort', 'SignedInteger', 'UnsignedShortWithValidity', 'SignedIntegerWithValidity'.

tag.name: Encoder-Unit
tag.description: The physical units of the data if decoded using this Scaling.

tag.name: Scaling-Type
tag.description: Type of the scaling: This defines how to convert from image data to physical quantities. Currently this is always 'LinearScaling' or 'NullScaling'.

tag.name: Scaling-Multiply
tag.description: If the Encoder is 'LinearScaling', this defines the factor by which the imagedata has to be multiplied.

tag.name: Scaling-Offset
tag.description: If the Encoder is 'LinearScaling', this defines an offset you have to add to the data after multiplication.

tag.name: Has-Invalid-Pixels
tag.description: 0 if this channel image is complete and has only valid pixels, 1 otherwise. Readers can rely on validity of all pixels if this is 0. Writers must set this to 1 unless they are sure that all pixels are valid.

tag.name: Nan-Marker
tag.description: Encoded value used to mark up an invalid pixel for the 'WithValidity' encoders. This field's value is either 0xffff for the unsigned-short encoder, or 0x7fff_ffff for the signed-integer encoder. Other values are unlikely to ever occur.
